    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>white long grain rice </strong>and <strong>cauliflower rice</strong> to a pot with a lid with 110ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [175ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[225ml</span>] cold water and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/korean-style-rose-chicken-with-sesame-soy-spinach-and-cauliflower-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>chicken breast strips</strong> and cook for 2-3 min on each side or until starting to brown</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/korean-style-rose-chicken-with-sesame-soy-spinach-and-cauliflower-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/korean-style-rose-chicken-with-sesame-soy-spinach-and-cauliflower-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken is starting to brown, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> with your <strong>tomato paste</strong> and <strong>gochujang paste</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/korean-style-rose-chicken-with-sesame-soy-spinach-and-cauliflower-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>Chinese rice wine </strong>with 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span><strong> boiled water </strong>and your <strong>clotted cream</strong></p><p>Season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper </strong>and cook for 5-6 min further or until cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>Korean-style rose chicken</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/korean-style-rose-chicken-with-sesame-soy-spinach-and-cauliflower-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once everything is nearly ready, reboil the kettle</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/korean-style-rose-chicken-with-sesame-soy-spinach-and-cauliflower-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong> then add to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over it so that it starts to wilt</p><p>Drain the <strong>spinach </strong>and squeeze any excess water out with the back of a spoon, then transfer it to a small bowl with your <strong>soy sauce</strong> and <strong>toasted</strong> <strong>sesame oil</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>sesame soy spinach</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/korean-style-rose-chicken-with-sesame-soy-spinach-and-cauliflower-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> Korean-style rose chicken </strong>with the <strong>cooked cauliflower rice </strong>and<strong> sesame soy spinach </strong>to the side</p><p>Top with your<strong> crispy onions</strong></p><p>Tip: For fancy presentation, press the rice into a small bowl and turn out</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
